The paper deals with egocentric vision, which is a subfield of computer vision. The proposed methodology involves the use of recurrent neural networks and attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in natural language processing and multimodal learning, indicating that the paper may also belong to the subcategories of machine learning and human-computer interaction. Therefore, the most likely subcategories are cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
